  "time_ut": 1660645742,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0dcf\u0daf - \u0db1\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dad\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba \u0db8\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dba \u0daf\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0da7\u0db8 \u0dc0\u0dc4\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sripada - Nallathanniya road continues to be closed",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Ranjith Alahakon, Assistant Director of Nuwara Eliya District Disaster Management Unit, says that the Maskeliya Sripada Nallathanniya road, which was hit by a landslide due to the heavy rains that fell in the water catchment areas of Maussakale in the last few days, has become active for further landslides, so the road has been closed.",
        "On that road, water flowed from Sri Pada Reserve to Nallathanniya Mohini Falls and Maussakale Reservoir. About half an acre of land above Seetha Gakula has now slipped and a part of the main road has also sunk towards Seetha Kagula.",
        "The assistant director said that a group of geologists from the National Building Research Institute inspected the place where the landslide occurred, and based on the recommendations given by the group of scientists, they took steps to further close the road.",
        "The assistant director said that due to the existing situation, it is dangerous for any passenger to walk, and due to the existing danger, Nallathanniya police officers have been put on duty at the place day and night.",
        "The 2022-2023 Sri Pada pilgrimage season is scheduled to start on Uduwap \u200b\u200bPoho day this year, and before the start of the pilgrimage season, on the recommendations of the geologists of the Mines and Geology Bureau, steps will be taken to bypass the landslide site and cut the road from another place, according to the executive office of the Norwood Road Development Authority. Engineer Ranga Devapriya said."
      ],
